<font color="#FF0000">THOUGHTS, OF A SORT...........</font><br>
<tt>Sat Oct  4 11:11:04 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Some thoughts on my mind.<br><br>
Last week I was asked if I &quot;liked&quot; combat. <br><br>
I replied ...just give me a battery of howitzers, a bank of radios, a set of sticks and charts, and a range protractor, and I would be ready to rock and roll...<br><br>
That's the way I felt during the coverage of the Gulf War.<br><br>
There is a macabre beauty in the machinery of combat and the heat of the chase. To ride with the grim reaper is the ultimate experience and the doorway into the primal form. I still carry the image of serpentine showers of Cobra minigun tracers against the blackness, slowly moving in undulating patterns of power and red hot beauty. I still feel the chest thumping impulse and fire flash of the big guns sending their message into the void.<br><br>
I admit I like it.<br><br>
I admit I hate it, at the same time. <br><br>
Pairs of opposites. 
<p><code>--   (art) </code><p>


